main event: Two globular dark blue objects with gray centers were observed in Chicago, Illinois, on June 11, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as appearing six inches in diameter,The observer reported the objects traveling at an estimated speed of 500 MPH,The observation lasted between 30 to 45 seconds,The objects changed course, one passing the other on the left before disappearing,The objects were thought to be at an altitude of approximately 6000 feet.
witness description: The observer had experience in judging altitudes and speeds of aircraft.
